Many such migrants to Australia, such as Prime Minister Julia Gillard, call themselves 'ten pound poms', because they paid ten pounds for their passage to Australia between 1945 and 1972 under an assisted migration scheme. Often combined with an adjective, particularly whingeing pom, a reference to migrants who complained about their adopted country. Often used in a sporting (especially cricket and rugby) context, with liberal use of 'pom' and 'Aussie' being used by the media; the term is often seen as unoffensive in this context, and instead as light-hearted banter by those who use it, but still possibly as offensive by those whom it is directed at.

dogans.hateful_meaning: In Canada, an Irish Catholic [19th century on; origin uncertain: perhaps from Dugan, an Irish surname].

doguns.hateful_meaning: In Canada, an Irish Catholic [19th century on; origin uncertain: perhaps from Dugan, an Irish surname].

dhimmis.hateful_meaning: Used by opponents of Islamisation and Muslim immigration to denote those who in their eyes facilitate it, with connotation of 'traitor'. Used in several languages in that sense, but originally an Islamic term referring to Jewish and Christian minorities.

diaper heads.hateful_meaning: An Arab, Indian Sikh or other individual of Middle Eastern or South Asian descent wearing traditional headdress such as turbans or keffiyehs. Sometimes used generically for all Islamic nations.

dindu.hateful_meaning: A derogatory contraction of the words "didn't do," popularized as a slur against black people as a mockery of regional pronunciation

dinges.hateful_meaning: A black person. Used in the novel 'To Kill a Mockingbird'.

Cushites.hateful_meaning: [1] A person of east African descent, from Cush (modern day Ethiopia or Sudan). [2] Any black African.

dagos.hateful_meaning: An Italian, Spaniard or Portuguese person, possibly derived from the Spanish name, 'Diego,' a corruption of the title Hidalgo (member of the Gentry, from Spanish > hijo de algo 'son of someone [important]' or the Sardinian language first person pronoun, dego)t.

darkies.hateful_meaning: A black person. The term may cause offense. though Randall Kennedy's Nigger: The Strange Career of a Troublesome Word notes that some judges have considered 'darky' a 'term of endearment.' In South Africa, it can be considered offensive (depending on the context), but is commonly used among black people to refer to other black people in a non-derogatory way.

degos.hateful_meaning: An Italian, Spaniard or Portuguese person, possibly derived from the Spanish name, 'Diego,' a corruption of the title Hidalgo (member of the Gentry, from Spanish > hijo de algo 'son of someone [important]' or the Sardinian language first person pronoun, dego)t.

curry munchers.hateful_meaning: A person of East Indian origin.

curry slurpers.hateful_meaning: A person of East Indian origin.

curry stinkers.hateful_meaning: A person of East Indian origin.

Cushis.hateful_meaning: [1] A person of east African descent, from Cush (modern day Ethiopia or Sudan). [2] Any black African.

crows.hateful_meaning: A black person, particularly a black woman.

cunts.hateful_meaning: [1] Comparing someone (usually Male) to female genitalia. A variant of "pussy", but generally regarded as far more offensive. [2] A despicable man (Australian English). Has a wide variety of usages and meaning across the English world. For instance, in Commonwealth Countries such as Britain, Australia or New Zealand it can be, and often is, used to refer positively to someone, while in Canada it is widely seen to be highly offensive.

cotton pickers.hateful_meaning: Originates from pre-Civil War US. Refers to the slaves who picked cotton all day at the plantations.

cow kissers.hateful_meaning: A person of Indian descent, from the worship of cows.

crackers.hateful_meaning: A poor Appalachian or poor Southerner, a white person, first used in the 19th century.
crackers.nonhateful_meaning: [1] Snack [2] Hacker [3] American musical group [4] British television show

Congoids.hateful_meaning: Some concatenation of Congo and mongoloid

coolies.hateful_meaning: [1] In North America, unskilled Asian labor, usually Chinese (originally used in 19th-century for Chinese railroad labor). Possibly from Hindi kuli, day laborer. [2] Racial epithet for Indo-Caribbean people, especially in Guyana, Trinidad and Tobago and South African Indians.

coonadians.hateful_meaning: A Canadian of African descent; sometimes applied to aboriginals

coons.hateful_meaning: A black person. Possibly from Portuguese barracco, a building constructed to hold slaves for sale (1837). Popularized by the song 'Zip Coon', played at Minstrel shows in the 1830s.

coconuts.hateful_meaning: [1] A person of Hispanic descent who's accused of acting white. [2] In, New Zealand/Australia, a Pacific Islander. Named after the coconut, the nut from the coconut palm. [3], In the UK, a black person who exhibits behaviour associated with caucasians. [4] In the USA, a black person trying to be 'white'. [5] In South Africa, a black person who acts white. [6], In Canada, an individual of South Asian (typically Dravidian) descent, who is accused of trying to be 'white'.

conchudas.hateful_meaning: [1] Comparing someone (usually Male) to female genitalia. A variant of "pussy", but generally regarded as far more offensive. [2] A despicable man (Australian English). Has a wide variety of usages and meaning across the English world. For instance, in Commonwealth Countries such as Britain, Australia or New Zealand it can be, and often is, used to refer positively to someone, while in Canada it is widely seen to be highly offensive.

closetfags.hateful_meaning: A person accused of being an homosexual

cocksuckers.hateful_meaning: A homosexual who engages in oral sex

clams.hateful_meaning: A Scientologist, referring to a passage about clam engrams in L. Ron Hubbard's 1952 book, What To Audit, later renamed The History Of Man

closet fags.hateful_meaning: A person accused of being an homosexual

chonkies.hateful_meaning: A person of Asian descent with perceived Caucasian mannerisms. Concatenation of Chinese and honky.

Christ killers.hateful_meaning: A Jew, an allusion to Jewish deicide. On occasion it can also be used as an anti-Italian slur on the basis the Romans, as ancestors of the present-day Italians, executed Jesus.
